{[%evp 0,56,41,19,35,-23,18,-17,9,19,28,37,36,28,37,-25,29,29,43,3,11,-18,1,21,
17,-14,23,-4,7,7,44,44,54,48,-49,-178,-157,-232,-250,-225,-225,-391,-386,-584,
-468,-520,-506,-572,-284,-284,-297,-297,-365,-429,-307,-307,-319,-512,-517]} 1.
d4 Nf6 2. c4 Nc6 {This is my favourite opening - Two Knights Tango. I have a
lot of important wins with it (of course some painfull loses too)} 3. Nf3 (3.
Nc3 {is more principled}) 3... e6 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. Bd2 O-O 6. Qc2 d6 {We
transpose to a 4.Qc2 Variation in Nimzo Indian} 7. O-O-O {In my opinion, this
move makes sense if Black's pawn is on h6 and White has a "hook"} (7. e3) (7.
a3 {are much more common moves}) 7... Qe7 {White wants to spend a tempo and
did not play a3, but Black is also not in a hurry to take on c3} ({The
immediate} 7... e5 $6 {is wrong due to} 8. Nd5 $1) 8. e3 a5 {Again, we see
dark square strategy. The exchange on c3 is inevitable, so I started to put my
pawns on the dark squares. Also, I am waiting for White to play a3.} 9. h3 e5 {
strange move with the idea g4. I think that this plan is just wrong.} 10. g4 {
This move is less powerful with Black's pawn on h7. Now the diagonal h1-a8 is
weakened too.} ({I calculated that} 10. Nd5 $6 {is not very good due to the
variation} Nxd5 11. cxd5 Bxd2+ 12. Qxd2 Nb4 13. a3 e4 $17 {and Black's
initiative is ovewhelming}) 10... Bxc3 {I wanted to wait for a3, but here I
decided that it was time for concrete actions.} (10... e4 11. Ne1) (10... exd4
11. exd4 Bxc3 12. Bxc3 Qe4 13. Qxe4 Nxe4 14. Be1 $14) 11. Bxc3 Nb4 12. Qb1 b6
$5 {This move is good, but too soft} (12... b5 $1 {With a big advantage for
Black.} 13. cxb5 Bb7 {[%cal Rb7e4] and Black is just winning.}) 13. dxe5 dxe5
14. Nxe5 Bb7 15. f3 Rfd8 16. Be2 Nd7 $1 {This is what my opponent missed. Here
White just collapsed.} 17. Rxd7 Rxd7 18. a3 Rdd8 $1 {Another cool move. White
has not threat} 19. axb4 axb4 20. Bd4 c5 21. Nxf7 {My opponent desperately
tries to complicate the position.} cxd4 22. Nxd8 Qxe3+ $19 23. Kd1 Rxd8 24. Qc1
Qe7 25. Bd3 Bxf3+ 26. Kc2 Bxh1 27. Qxh1 Qe3 28. Qd1 Rf8 0-1

