1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. Qc2 d6 6. Bd2 O-O 7. a3 {I think
that this is the critical line for the evaluation of the variation.} Bxc3 8.
Bxc3 {In this position, Black is at a crossroads. There are three possible
moves, and all of them have pros and cons.} Re8 {In my recent games, I prefer
this move.} (8... Qe7 9. e3 (9. e4 $1 {is unpleasant, because of the variation}
e5 10. d5 Nd4 11. Nxd4 exd4 12. Bxd4 Qxe4+ 13. Qxe4 $14 {White has a better
endgame thanks to his bishop pair}) 9... e5 10. d5 Nb8 {If Black has time to
play Bg4, he will be just fine.} 11. Nd2 $1 {This move is very strong. Now
Black has a problem finding a good square for his light square bishop} c6 12.
dxc6 Nxc6 13. Bd3 h6 (13... Nd4 $5 {I tried this move against GM Hammer and
managed to make a draw, but now without some problems.} 14. Qb1 Ne6 (14... Bg4)
15. b4) 14. O-O (14. Ne4 Be6 15. Nxf6+ Qxf6 16. O-O {0-1 (27) Bok,B (2624)
-Karthikeyan,M (2606) Chess. com INT 2021}) 14... d5 15. b4 $16 {I lost quite
painfully, without any single chance. 1-0 (29) Dreev,A (2698)-Arnaudov, P 
(2476) Plovdiv 2012 CBM 148 [Arnau]}) (8... a5 {This is too slow} 9. e4 e5 10.
d5 Nb8 {This position could be acceptable for Black if White's pawn comes to
e4 in two moves. Now White is better.} 11. Nd2 $14) 9. e3 e5 10. d5 Ne7 {
One other benefit of 8... Re8 is that the e7-square is avaialble for the
knight.} 11. e4 {In this structure, White chooses a structure where Black's
rook is misplaced on e8.} Nh5 12. Nd2 f5 (12... c6 {Is another way to handle
the position.}) 13. O-O-O Rf8 14. g3 Nf6 (14... f4 15. Be2) 15. Bd3 fxe4 (15...
Ng4 {I calculated this move, but somehow choose to enter solid, but passive
position instead} 16. Rdf1 f4 17. Nb3 Bd7) 16. Nxe4 Nxe4 17. Bxe4 Bf5 18. Rhf1
Qd7 19. f4 Bxe4 20. Qxe4 exf4 21. Rxf4 Rxf4 (21... Ng6 22. Rxf8+ Rxf8 $14) 22.
Qxf4 Ng6 23. Qe3 a5 24. Re1 b6 25. h4 Qg4 26. Qe6+ Qxe6 27. Rxe6 Kf7 {The
endgame is not easy at all, but somehow I manage to hold it against my famous
opponent.} 28. h5 Nf8 29. Re4 g6 30. Rf4+ Kg8 31. h6 Nd7 32. Bg7 Re8 33. Kc2
Nc5 34. g4 Nd7 35. Kd3 Nc5+ 36. Kd2 Nd7 37. b3 Nc5 38. b4 axb4 39. axb4 Nd7 40.
Kd3 Ra8 41. Kc2 Ra3 42. Bc3 Ra2+ 43. Kb3 Ra8 44. Rf1 Ra7 45. g5 Ra8 46. Ra1 $2
Rxa1 47. Bxa1 Kf7 48. Ka4 Ke8 49. Kb5 Kd8 50. Bd4 Kc8 51. Bf6 Kb7 52. Bg7 Kc8
53. Ka6 Kb8 54. Bf6 Ka8 55. Bd4 Kb8 56. Kb5 Kc8 57. Be3 Kb7 58. c5 bxc5 59.
bxc5 Nxc5 60. Bxc5 dxc5 61. Kxc5 Kc8 62. Kc6 Kd8 63. d6 1/2-1/2

