1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d6 5. Nf3 Nbd7 6. Bd2 e5 {Black didn't
waste time for castle} 7. a3 Bxc3 8. Bxc3 e4 $1 (8... Qe7 {With the knight on
d7, we are not putting pressure on White's center and sometimes Qe7 is just
too slow. Of course, you can choose a setup with b6 or with Nf8-g6, but It
seems a bit slow to me.} 9. e3 $1) 9. Nd2 e3 $1 {very nice pawn sacrifice. We
sacrificed the pawn for ruining White's structure, for not giving White a
chance to develop his pieces and} 10. fxe3 O-O 11. h3 Nh5 $1 12. O-O-O Ng3 13.
Rg1 {When you look at the f1-bishop, you realize that Black's position is very
good.} f5 14. e4 Qg5 15. exf5 Nf6 16. e4 Nfxe4 17. Bd3 Nf2 18. Rde1 Nxd3+ 19.
Qxd3 Bxf5 $19 20. Qe3 Qg6 {Of course, we are not exchanging the queens} 21. Qf3
Rae8 22. Qd5+ Kh8 23. Qxb7 Ne2+ 24. Rxe2 Rxe2 25. Qxc7 Qg3 26. Nf3 Qf4+ 27. Nd2
Qe3 0-1

