increase the pressure with simple moves such as ...Nf6, ...Qd7, ...Rae8, and ..
.Na5.} 16. Re1 Nf6 17. Bf2 Qd7 18. Nf1 Na5 19. Bh4 Rae8 20. Rxe8 Qxe8 $19 {
[%csl Rc4] Without making obvious mistakes, Carlsen is already losing. The
c4-pawn cannot be protected. Later on, Nakamura managed to convert his
advantage.} 21. Bxf6 Rxf6 22. Qf3 Re6 23. Rb1 Bxc4 24. Bxc4 Nxc4 25. a4 Kg7 26.
Qb7+ Qf7 27. Qa6 Re7 28. Rb8 Kh6 29. h3 Qe6 30. Ra8 Nd2 31. Rd8 Nxf1 32. Qxf1
Qe3+ 33. Kh2 Re4 34. Rxd6 Qxf4+ 35. Qxf4+ Rxf4 36. a5 Rc4 37. Ra6 Rxc3 38. Rxa7
