1. d4 f5 2. c4 Nf6 3. g3 e6 4. Bg2 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 Bxd2+ 6. Nxd2 Nc6 7. Ngf3 O-O 8.
O-O d6 9. Qb3 Kh8 10. Qc3 e5 11. e3 (11. dxe5 dxe5 12. Nxe5 $2 Nxe5 13. Qxe5
Qxd2) 11... a5 12. b3 (12. a3 a4) 12... Qe8 13. a3 Qh5 14. h4 (14. dxe5 dxe5
15. Nxe5 Nxe5 16. Qxe5 Ng4) (14. b4 $2 e4 15. Ne1 axb4) 14... Ng4 15. Ng5 Bd7
16. f3 Nf6 17. f4 e4 18. Rfd1 h6 19. Nh3 d5 $1 {Now is when the game becomes
similar with the previous one.} 20. Nf1 Ne7 {Threatening ...a5-a4.} 21. a4 {
With the black light-squaared bishop on board and the white one very passive,
the weakness on a4 tells.} Nc6 22. Rd2 Nb4 23. Bh1 Qe8 24. Rg2 dxc4 25. bxc4 {
Consistent, but ineffective. White will not manage to keep the control over d5
for too long.} Bxa4 26. Nf2 Bd7 27. Nd2 b5 $1 28. Nd1 Nd3 $1 29. Rxa5 b4 30.
Rxa8 bxc3 $5 (30... Qxa8 $17) 31. Rxe8 c2 32. Rxf8+ Kh7 33. Nf2 c1=Q+ 34. Nf1
Ne1 $1 35. Rh2 Qxc4 36. Rb8 Bb5 37. Rxb5 Qxb5 38. g4 Nf3+ 39. Bxf3 exf3 40.
gxf5 Qe2 $1 41. d5 (41. Rh3 Ng4 $1) (41. Nh3 Ng4 $3 42. Rxe2 fxe2) 41... Kg8
42. h5 Kh7 43. e4 Nxe4 44. Nxe4 Qxe4 45. d6 cxd6 46. f6 gxf6 47. Rd2 Qe2 48.
Rxe2 fxe2 49. Kf2 exf1=Q+ (49... e1=Q+ 50. Kxe1 Kg7 51. Kf2 Kf7 52. Ke3 Ke6 53.
Ke4 d5+) 50. Kxf1 Kg7 51. Kf2 Kf7 52. Ke3 Ke6 53. Ke4 d5+ 0-1

