16. Nd2 (16. a4 Bb7 17. Ba3 Rf6 18. Rab1 Qc7 $36 {[%csl Gb7][%cal Gf6h6]})
16... Nxd2 17. Bxd2 {1/2 (26) Flear,G (2431)-Adams,M (2716) Tornelo INT 2021}
e5 $146 18. f3 Be6 19. Be1 exd4 20. cxd4 Ne7 {The poor Ba2 makes it difficult
for White to advance the central pawns, while Black's passers seem dangerous.})
(11. Ne4 b5 12. Nxf6+ Qxf6 13. Qe4 Bb7 14. Bd3 g6 15. dxc5 Nb4 16. Qe5 Qxe5 17.
Nxe5 Nxd3 18. Nxd3 Rfd8 19. Ne5 Bc7 20. Nf3 Rd3) 11... Qxd3 12. Bxd3 Bxc3 13.
bxc3 Na5 {offers Black a sufficient counter-play against White's weak c-pawns.
For instance,} 14. Rb1 Rd8 15. Bc2 Bd7 16. e4 Rac8 {Cameron,S - Lukasevicius,P
ICCF email 2018}) 6... Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. Nf3 (9. Ne2 Qc7 10. Ba2
b6 11. O-O Ba6 12. Bb2 Rd8 13. Rc1 (13. Re1 Nc6 14. Ng3 Na5 15. e4 Bc4 16. Bxc4
Nxc4 17. Bc1 Ne8 $1 {Avoiding the nasty pin/ and transferring the knight on d6/
}) 13... Nc6 14. c4 cxd4 15. exd4 b5 $1 {This move was suggested by me in the
book, and I still find it the most convincing - it is important to fix the
pawn structure.}) 9... Qc7 10. Be2 Rd8 $5 {I believe, this move offers Black a
more comfortable play than after 11...b6, as was recently tested in a few
games of Wesley So} (10... b6 11. Bb2 (11. O-O Ba6) 11... Ba6 (11... cxd4 12.
cxd4 Ba6 13. O-O Bxe2 14. Qxe2 Nbd7 15. e4 Rac8 16. Rfc1 (16. Rac1 Qb7 17. Nd2
b5 $11 {[%cal Ga7a6,Gd7b6]}) 16... Qb7 17. Re1 h6 (17... b5 18. Rab1 a6 19. a4
Rc6) 18. Rab1 Rc7 19. Nd2 Rfc8 20. Nf1 {1/2 (84) So,W (2770)-Giri,A (2780)
Bucharest 2021} Ne8) 12. c4 cxd4 13. Nxd4 Nbd7 14. O-O Rac8 15. Nb5) 11. O-O
Nc6 12. Bb2 (12. Qc2 e5 13. dxe5 Nxe5 14. c4 Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 Bg4 {Black has no
problems.}) 12... e5 13. Qc2 Bg4 14. dxe5 (14. h3 Bh5 15. dxe5 Nxe5 16. Nxe5
Bxe2 17. Qxe2 Qxe5 18. c4 Qe6 19. Rfd1 b6 20. Qf3 Ne4 $11 {0-1 (40) Evengroen,
H (2160) -Saravanan,V (2326) Dieren 2018}) 14... Nxe5 15. c4 Nxf3+ 16. gxf3 Bh3
17. Rfd1 Qe7 18. Kh1 Rxd1+ 19. Rxd1 Rd8 20. Rg1 Ne8 {The idea is to lock the
long diagonal with ...f7-f6. White's bishops pair is fully compensated by
Black's superior pawn structure.} *

